AB  - In the context of the rapid popularization of domestic innovative terminals and the increasing demand for cybersecurity, digital twin technology has opened up a new path for the trustworthy and controllable security management of information technology innovation terminals. This paper systematically reviews the theory and key technologies of digital twin, proposes a digital twin model for information technology innovation terminals, and supports dynamic security management and autonomous decision-making throughout the entire lifecycle of the terminals. This model not only realizes real-time security state perception, risk warning and active protection, but also builds a technical system with 'trusted identity verification' and 'controllable behavior monitoring' as the core, providing a strong guarantee for the stable operation and data security of government and enterprise systems. © 2025 IEEE.
