AB  - Air pollution is a top concern in major cities of developing countries. Air Quality Monitoring systems with impressive operational procedures in domestic premises are key to the creation of a sustainable pollution free green port In this article, the authors propose to build an air environment monitoring system at seaports in Vietnam based on LoRaWAnwireless communication technology. The system includes sensors that collect parameters such as CO, SO2, NO2, and PM2.5 at each intermediate station. Use the Real-time Data Transfer algorithms (RT-DTWOA) to optimize the transmission and reception process and calculate the AQI index. Experimental results of the system are stable, cost-effective and accurate on maps at the monitoring center. © 2024 IEEE.
