AB  - The operation of the distribution network mainly depends on the lines, grids, equipment, and customer electricity usage in the distribution network. The safe and reasonable operation of the entire process is the key to the success of the distribution network operation. Analyzing the relevant indicators of distribution network operation can provide decision-making data support for the power supply management department. The monitoring of operational indicators in the distribution network is the fundamental guarantee for the safe, orderly, healthy, and efficient coordination of power grid operations, which can significantly improve the service and management capabilities of business departments. Digital twin technology provides high-precision data base support for operational monitoring and control in the power grid, and ensures the real-time and effectiveness of data models based on intelligent collection terminals. Grid operation and regulatory personnel can observe and analyze the operation of power equipment and facilities in reality through digital twin models. And use the basic algorithms of the model to deduce and predict real power data, and make plans for potential faults and risks based on the results of the deduction and prediction. This article proposes a distribution network operation analysis method based on the digital twin model. The digital twin model is applied to the analysis and mining of distribution network operation data, and relevant demonstration applications are carried out. The analysis method is optimized and improved based on the application effect. © 2023 SPIE.
