AB  - The operation of an overhead crane system is influenced by various factors that induce vibrations in the crane bridge. This paper addresses the vibration control problem of a crane bridge system modeled using partial differential equations, where system states are not fully measurable. To enhance real-time monitoring and control, an IoT-enabled framework is introduced. A high-gain observer is designed to estimate the unmeasurable states, enabling an event-triggered controller that reduces communication burden while optimizing system efficiency. System stability is rigorously analyzed using Lyapunov theory, and mathematical validation ensures that event-triggered time intervals remain strictly positive, successfully avoiding the Zeno phenomenon. Finally, simulations confirm the effectiveness of the proposed IoT-driven control scheme. © 1975-2011 IEEE.
