AB  - Monitoring vessel traffic on a global scale is a complex and challenging task. The large number of moving vessels and the complexity of monitoring their position and forecasting their route in real-time require novel, advanced and highly scalable big-data mechanisms. In this work a digital twin for constant maritime situational awareness on a global scale is presented. The described multi-layered system is able to visualize maritime traffic in real-time, based on data from the Automatic Identification System (AIS), while also providing forecasts of future movement based on machine learning and deep learning techniques. The system is validated using real streaming AIS data from around the globe to demonstrate its performance, scalability and parallelization efficiency. © 2023 ACM.
