UR  - https://www.scopus.com/pages/publications/105031683853?origin=resultslist
AB  - The Smart Bollard is a cutting-edge innovation designed to enhance port safety and efficiency by providing real-time monitoring of mooring line loads. Installed permanently on quays, it measures the structural movement induced by mooring line tension, offering accurate data on load forces to port authorities, terminal operators, and vessels. Unlike traditional bollards, the Smart Bollard significantly improves risk mitigation, particularly during severe weather conditions such as high waves and gusty winds, thereby preventing accidents and damage. Following years of extensive research, testing, and engineering, the Smart Bollard has been rigorously validated through finite element analysis and computational simulations, demonstrating its structural integrity and performance. The integration of the Smart Bollard with MoorControl software provides comprehensive data visualization, enabling operators to optimize port operations, enhance safety, and accommodate larger vessels. With successful trials in the Port of Rotterdam and ongoing testing in other major European ports, the Smart Bollard represents a significant leap forward in digitizing port management and advancing the maritime industry's operational capabilities. © Australasian Coasts and Ports 2025.All rights reserved.
