AB  - Container terminals often face security issues such as unauthorized access and loss of goods, leading to operational disputes. This study presents the design and development of a container security monitoring system that integrates door access detection for logistics containers using IoT and LoRaWAN technologies. The system integrates magnetic sensors, a LoRa-based end node, a cloud platform, and a mobile application to monitor container door access status. Functional testing was conducted in a controlled laboratory environment using various door materials, and the results showed 100% detection accuracy. Additionally, the system detected door separation events with a minimum sensor reading distance of 27.41 mm. The current implementation serves as a prototype and has not yet been equipped with industrial-grade components. This prototype demonstrates the feasibility of enhancing physical container security by enabling automated detection of unauthorized door access events and real-time alerts. © 2025 IEEE.
