C7  - 116128
DO  - 10.1088/1361-6501/ae1fa5
UR  - https://www.scopus.com/pages/publications/105033877799?origin=resultslist
AB  - The prediction of the remaining useful life (RUL) of the bearings in quay crane (QC) hoisting reducers is crucial for ensuring the safe operation of port equipment. Aiming at the influence of random correlation among components and dynamic load impact on bearing life, this study proposes a RUL prediction method for QC reduction gearbox bearings that integrates dynamic load impact extraction and multi-component collaborative degradation modeling. Firstly, the bidirectional long short-term memory network is utilized to extract the effective transient load impact components from the stress signals of the forestay. Secondly, in combination with the degradation correlation among components, a multivariable Wiener process model that simultaneously considers dynamic load impact and random correlation is constructed; furthermore, the conditional activated particle Filter algorithm is adopted to jointly estimate the model parameters and hidden states; Ultimately, the degradation trajectory is dynamically updated based on real-time monitoring data to achieve RUL prediction. The correctness of the proposed method was verified by using the full life data of the bearings of the QC hoisting reducer at a certain port in Shanghai collected in the NetCMAS system. The results show that the proposed method is more superior compared with the traditional analysis model, providing a new idea for the degradation modeling and life prediction of bearings. © 2025 IOP Publishing Ltd. All rights, including for text and data mining, AI training, and similar technologies, are reserved.
