AB  - Overhead cranes are essential construction machinery when, for example, transporting loads in construction areas, factories, and docks. To achieve anti swing control of an overhead crane, a sway angle must be estimated. We show a soft sensor to estimate the angle by using two microphones. Our method achieves contact less sensing, high flexibility of installation, low realization cost, and easy maintenance. The method employs a phase difference of acoustic signals observed by the two microphones. Moreover, we show an algorithm to obtain the angle from the phase difference by using Newton's method. In the experimental results, we demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed method. © 2020 IEEE.
