AB  - Due to the harsh working environment, casualties, and severe shortage of skilled operators associated with crawler cranes, a remote control system was developed. First, based on the five-dimensional digital twin model, the overall architecture of a digital twin state monitoring system for crawler cranes was proposed, and a digital twin platform was established. Secondly, various sensors were installed on the crawler cranes to obtain their real-time motion parameters. Then, a highly low-latency control system was developed based on the CAN bus and 5G, enabling intelligent assisted manipulation and remote control of the crawler cranes. Finally, the crawler crane's operating status and key parameters were monitored using the digital twin and real-time data transmission. Finally, the digital twin model and real-time data transmission were used to monitor the operating status and key parameters of the crawler crane, and the data was fed back to the status monitoring system. Response delay tests and hook control accuracy tests were also conducted to verify the real-time and reliability of the crawler crane status remote control system. © 2025 SPIE.
