TI  - A grab bucket detection algorithm for ship unloaders in intelligent port monitoring
PY  - 2025
T2  - Proceedings of SPIE - The International Society for Optical Engineering
VL  - 13976
C7  - 139760W
DO  - 10.1117/12.3082871
UR  - https://www.scopus.com/pages/publications/105026336879?origin=resultslist
AB  - In the advancement of modern port infrastructure, the accurate and efficient operation of ship unloader grab buckets is critical to enhancing overall port performance and operational safety. Traditional manual observation methods are not only inefficient but also pose significant safety risks, falling short of the requirements for intelligent port systems. To overcome these limitations, we propose an advanced grab detection algorithm based on progressive features Pyramid network, called ACSSD. The framework combines the benefits of a single-lens multi-box detector (SSD) and the feature pyramid network (FPN) is used to construct a robust multi-scale feature extraction architecture. In addition, a deformable convolution is added to dynamically adapt the bounding box generation of the response. The attitude of grab bucket is changed to improve the robustness and detection accuracy of the model. overall experiments show that ACSSD algorithm can realize the realtime detection speed of 47 frames/frame. Second, the recall rate is as high as 96.84%. These results demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed algorithm in terms of balance accuracy and stability efficiency, making it ideal for real-world port operations and contributing to broader development intelligent logistics system. © 2025 COPYRIGHT SPIE.
